Also here, nature has its example: water striders are water-walking insects thanks to their non-wetting legs32–34. These legs are covered with a large number of tiny hair35 as shown in Supplementary Note 2 and Supplementary Fig. 2. Each of these tiny hairs have nano-grooves to possess water resistance. Due to this unique combination of hierarchical micro and nanostructure on the legs surface, the dimples created by the legs on the water can be up to 4.38 ±\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
